	     Johannesburg - Heavy rain has caused flooding in the Benoni area, on Johannesburg's East Rand on Thursday, paramedics said. Numerous collisions were reported, most of them minor, because of the rain and flooding, ER24 said. No injuries were reported. The N12 highway was affected as well as the Snake Road off-ramp and O'Reilly Merry Street. Heavy rains caused flooding on the N12 in Benoni. Fortunately no-one was injured. pic.twitter.com/PbdrYOB7uM  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  